obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `T HE REVENUE, BOMBAY, 1842`
  line __________
  line `A CT N O.13 OF 1842`
  line _________
  line `Passed by the Hon’ble the President of the Council of India in Council, on the 28 th of October, 1842, with`
  line `the assent of the Right hon’ble the Governor General of India.`
  line `A n Act to enable the holders of Revenue which has been alienated to them by the State, to collect that`
  line `Revenue within the Presidency of Bombay.`
  line `I. Whereas it is expedient to authorize the grant by the Governor in Council of Bombay, at his`
  line `discretion, of Commissions to certain Jageerdars, and others, by virtue of which such persons shall posses`
  line `increased powers for collecting the Revenue due to them; —`
  line `It is hereby enacted, that it shall be lawful for the Governor in Council of Bomb ay, to grant any`
  line `Jageerdar, Surinjamdar, Inamdar, or other person holding Lands or Villages the Revenue of which has been`
  line `alienated to him by the State, a Commission conferring upon him authority for the collection of such`
  line `Revenue by the powers hereinafter mentioned, or such of them as shall be specified in the Commission in`
  line `addition to the powers now exercisable by law.`
  line `II. And it is hereby enacted, that such Commission, which shall be drawn out according to the form of`
  line `the annexed Schedule A, shall be g ranted or withheld, and, when granted, shall be liable to be withdrawn`
  line `at the pleasure of Government, and that it may, if the Governor in Council of Bombay see fit, be issued to`
  line `one or more Agents of such holder of alienated Revenue as well as to the hold er in person.`
  line `III. And it is hereby enacted, that the holder of such Commission shall have authority to demand`
  line `security for the payment of the Revenue, in respect of the Lands or Villages specified in the Commission,`
  line `and if the same be not furnished, to ta ke such precaution as the Collector is authorized to make under`
  line `Section XI, Regulation XVII, of 1827, Bombay Code.`
  line `I V. And it is hereby enacted, that the holder of such Commission shall have authority to send Mohussuls`
  line `on Defaulters under the Provisions of Clauses 2,3, and 5, Section XII, Regulation XVII of 1827, Bombay`
  line `Code, provided that one foot Mohussul only be employed in each case, and that the Mohussulee shall cease`
  line `on the enforcement of any other remedy for t he collection of the Revenue, except the taking of such security`
  line `as aforesaid.`
  line `V. And it is hereby enacted, that the holder of any such Commission shall be authorized to attach the`
  line `property of persons making default in the payment of such Revenue as afore said, making an immediate`
  line `report to the Collector or his Assistant of the his having done so, and should the demand on account of`
  line `which the attachment may be made app ear to the Collector or his Assistant to b e just, he shall give orders`
  line `for the sale of suc h property, and the sale shall be conducted agreeably to the Provisions of clause VII,`
  line `Section XII, Regulation XVII, of 1827, Bombay Code, except in cases in which the holder of the`
  line `Commission by whom the attachment has been made shall be a Jageerdar, Sur injamdar or Inamdar, vested`
  line `by Regulation XIII, of 1830, with Civil jurisdiction and with power to execute his own decrees or his`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-2
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Page 2`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  sourcePage 2
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `Agents, when the sale shall be conducted by him and not by the Collector and his subordinate Revenue`
  line Officers.
  line `VI. And it is hereby enacted, that all compulsory process under this Act shall cease on the alleged`
  line `defaulter furnishing security to the holder of the Commission or to the Collector or Assistant Collector of`
  line `the District, to institute a suit within 15 days in a com petent Court for the purpose of trying the demand`
  line `and to pay the amount which may be decreed against him with costs and interest in such Court, provided`
  line `that such suits in which any one of the privileged clas ses established by Regulation XXIX, of 1827, Se ctions`
  line `III, and IV, and by Regulation VII, of 1830, Bombay Code, may be the defendant, shall be tried before the`
  line `Collector and his Assistants, any thing in Regulations I, and XVI, of 1831, notwithstanding. And any holder`
  line `of any such Commission as aforesai d by h imself or his Agents proceeding with any compulsory process`
  line `under this Act after the furnishing of such security as aforesaid, or after the due tender thereof, shall forfeit`
  line `three times the amount of the Revenue sought to be recovered by such compuls ory process.`
  line `VII. And it is hereby enacted, that if the Revenue or rent payable to a Jageerdar or other holder of`
  line `Government alienated lands or villages shall have been fixed by a Government Officer before the grant of`
  line `the Land in free tenure, or if the rent or Revenue tend ered by any Ryut or other person be at the usual rate`
  line `payable according to the custom of the Village and P urgunna as declared by the K oolkurnee and other`
  line `Local Officers of Revenue, the enforcement of a demand by any holder of a Commission under this Act of`
  line `an excess of rent or Revenue beyond the amount due as above provided shall be deemed to the extortion,`
  line `and the person against whom such demand sh all have been enforced shall obtain upon any judgement being`
  line `passed after regular or summary trial three times the amount of any such excessive demand as damages for`
  line `the same. Provided, however, that nothing herein prescribed or con ta ined shall prevent a holder of`
  line `alienated Lands or Villages from instituting a suit in any court of competent jurisdiction for the purpose`
  line `of establishing his claim to re - assess the Lands or re - settle the Revenue of any Ryut or other who may be`
  line `paying less than the full Jum a to which he is justly liable, and upon such holder obtaining a decree`
  line `adjudging to him such power the demand made by him under such decree, shall, if conformable thereto be`
  line `deemed a legal demand for arrears, and shall be leviable by the same process a s is above arrears.`
  line `VIII. And it is hereby enacted, that the power conferred by such Commission shall extend to the`
  line `enforcement of the payment of the Revenue of the current season and of the season next immediately`
  line `preceding, and not to that of former year s.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
